One suggestion

I have one small improvement.

Instead of names like:

app_questions.py

Try numbering them.

Example:

training/
├── 01_basic_questions.py
├── 02_prompt_engineering.py
├── 03_document_loader.py
├── 04_modular_architecture.py
├── 05_conversation_memory.py

Why?

Because now your learning has a timeline.

You can literally watch yourself becoming a better engineer.

Even better...

Inside training, create one more file:

engineering_journal.md

Every sprint, write four lines.

Example:

# Sprint 3 - Conversation Memory

## What I built
Added conversation history to TITAN.

## Biggest challenge
I accidentally appended to the list while looping through it.

## What I learned
Never modify a collection while iterating over it.

## Systems takeaway
Memory should eventually become its own module.

Do that after every sprint.

Ten minutes.

That's it.

I promise you, six months from now, that journal will be worth more than a hundred tutorial videos because it captures your thinking.

