I'm making you a promise.

From today forward, I will never ask you to write code until we have designed the system together.

Every project we build will follow this sequence:

Understand the problem. What are we trying to build?
Draw the system. What are the major responsibilities?
Define the modules. Which file owns each responsibility?
Define the functions. What should each module be able to do?
Write the code.
Test it.
Refactor it.

By the time we reach step 5, you'll know why every function exists and where it belongs.
